snippet.textDisplay:
Novak deserves a fair go. How many Australians lost their jobs? Do you think that is fair? This new omicron variant cannot be compared to the delta variant. It presents a completely different set of challenges. "Knowledge is not enough, we must apply".

I certainly do not condone his behaviour, but we have to look at the bigger picture. How many annual deaths can be accredited to respiratory diseases associated with the seasonal influenza? Yet, people will catch the flu and go out into the public and spread the virus. The current explosion in omicron cases is attributed to the behaviour of the many, not the few. Trying to place the blame on Novak, or any other unvaccinated individual is simply counterproductive. We can see this by observing the current situation.

Humanity is facing so many challenges at he moment, we need to unite and face these challenges together. We invest so much energy on fighting/competing against each other, and as a result we manage to destroy everything around us. What world will we leave behind? Why can't we just work together united as one, for the benefit of our entire species. Instead of fighting each other, let’s complement one another. Mutual benefit can only be achieved through mutual respect. Peace, stay safe!
